{
  "page": "Viserys Plumm",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Plumm\" title=\"House Plumm\"><img alt=\"House Plumm.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/c/cf/House_Plumm.svg/50px-House_Plumm.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/c/cf/House_Plumm.svg/75px-House_Plumm.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/c/cf/House_Plumm.svg/100px-House_Plumm.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\"><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> Lord</span><br />Viserys Plumm</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Plumm\" title=\"House Plumm\"><img alt=\"House Plumm.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/c/cf/House_Plumm.svg/50px-House_Plumm.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/c/cf/House_Plumm.svg/75px-House_Plumm.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/c/cf/House_Plumm.svg/100px-House_Plumm.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Viserys_Plumm_by_Riotarttherite.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Viserys Plumm by Riotarttherite.jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/98/Viserys_Plumm_by_Riotarttherite.jpg/350px-Viserys_Plumm_by_Riotarttherite.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"355\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/98/Viserys_Plumm_by_Riotarttherite.jpg/525px-Viserys_Plumm_by_Riotarttherite.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/9/98/Viserys_Plumm_by_Riotarttherite.jpg/700px-Viserys_Plumm_by_Riotarttherite.jpg 2x\" /></a><div>Viserys Plumm, by Riotarttherite ©</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Lord\" title=\"Lord\">Lord</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Plumm\" title=\"House Plumm\">House Plumm</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Westermen\" title=\"Westermen\">Westermen</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_176_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">176&#160;AC</a> or <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_177_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">177&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Date_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Date-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\nIn or after <a href=\"/index.php/212_AC\" title=\"212 AC\">212&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Date_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Date-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Fathers</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Ossifer_Plumm\" title=\"Ossifer Plumm\">Ossifer Plumm</a> <small>(officially)</small><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_baelor_i_.28the_sisters_of_baelor_i.29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_baelor_i_.28the_sisters_of_baelor_i.29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></li><li>King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_IV_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon IV Targaryen\">Aegon IV Targaryen</a> <small>(rumored)</small><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_baelor_i_.28the_sisters_of_baelor_i.29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_baelor_i_.28the_sisters_of_baelor_i.29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Mother</th><td>\nPrincess <a href=\"/index.php/Elaena_Targaryen\" title=\"Elaena Targaryen\">Elaena Targaryen</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_baelor_i_.28the_sisters_of_baelor_i.29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_baelor_i_.28the_sisters_of_baelor_i.29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Issue</th><td>\nSons<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Mystery_Knight\" title=\"The Mystery Knight\">The Mystery Knight</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Viserys Plumm</b> was the head of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Plumm\" title=\"House Plumm\">House Plumm</a> during the reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Aerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aerys I Targaryen\">Aerys I Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Quotes_about_Viserys\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes about Viserys</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Family\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Family</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Viserys_Plumm&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Viserys's father, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Ossifer_Plumm\" title=\"Ossifer Plumm\">Ossifer Plumm</a>, was a wealthy but aged man when he wed Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Elaena_Targaryen\" title=\"Elaena Targaryen\">Elaena Targaryen</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_176_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">176&#160;AC</a>. He is said to have died during the <a href=\"/index.php/Bedding\" title=\"Bedding\">bedding</a>, after seeing his wife naked for the first time.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_baelor_i_.28the_sisters_of_baelor_i.29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_baelor_i_.28the_sisters_of_baelor_i.29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Nevertheless, Elaena did conceive, and Viserys was eventually born. However, rumors later suggested that Lord Ossifer had died before he was able to consummate the marriage, and that Viserys instead had been fathered by King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_IV_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon IV Targaryen\">Aegon IV Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_baelor_i_.28the_sisters_of_baelor_i.29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_baelor_i_.28the_sisters_of_baelor_i.29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc12.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc12.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> The claim that Ossifer fathered a child after his death led to the saying that he had had \"a cock six feet long\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Maynard_Plumm\" title=\"Maynard Plumm\">Maynard Plumm</a> claimed to be distantly related to Lord Viserys, though doubted the lord would admit to it.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Viserys_Plumm&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Viserys_Plumm&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>When Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a> tells Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a> that there is no worry that her son King <a href=\"/index.php/Tommen_Baratheon\" title=\"Tommen Baratheon\">Tommen I Baratheon</a> could consummate his marriage with <a href=\"/index.php/Margaery_Tyrell\" title=\"Margaery Tyrell\">Margaery Tyrell</a>, as Tommen is \"much too young\", Cersei replies that <a href=\"/index.php/Ossifer_Plumm\" title=\"Ossifer Plumm\">Ossifer Plumm</a> \"was much too dead\", but that didn't stop him from fathering a child. She intends to explain that any child of Margaery's could be recognized as being fathered by Tommen, even if it was physically impossible for him to impregnate her.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc12.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc12.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Viserys_Plumm&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a> encounters <a href=\"/index.php/Ben_Plumm\" title=\"Ben Plumm\">Brown Ben Plumm</a>, commander of the <a href=\"/index.php/Second_Sons\" title=\"Second Sons\">Second Sons</a>, and speculates that he is descended from a younger son of Viserys Plumm. He guesses that <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a>'s <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragons</a> were fond of Ben,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> which amuses Ben as it is true,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> and that he knows why. When Ben says his mother said his father had \"a drop of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">dragon blood</a>\", Tyrion replies, \"Two drops. That, or a cock six foot long\",<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> suggesting that Tyrion believes the rumors about Ossifer's posthumous child being fathered by <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_IV_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon IV Targaryen\">Aegon IV Targaryen</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes_about_Viserys\">Quotes about Viserys</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Viserys_Plumm&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes about Viserys\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Egg</b>: Plumm&#8230;are you kin to Lord Viserys Plumm, ser?<br />\n<b>Maynard</b>: Distantly, though I doubt that his lordship would admit to it. One might say that he is of the sweet Plumms, whilst I am of the sour.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_V_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon V Targaryen\">Aegon \"Egg\" Targaryen</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Maynard_Plumm\" title=\"Maynard Plumm\">Maynard Plumm</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Ossifer_Plumm\" title=\"Ossifer Plumm\">Ossifer Plumm</a> was much too dead, but that did not stop him fathering a child, did it?<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/House_Plumm\" title=\"House Plumm\">House Plumm</a> is sworn to <a href=\"/index.php/Casterly_Rock\" title=\"Casterly Rock\">Casterly Rock</a>, and as it happens I know a bit of its history. Your branch sprouted from a stone spit across the <a href=\"/index.php/Narrow_sea\" title=\"Narrow sea\">narrow sea</a>, no doubt. A younger son of Viserys Plumm, I'd wager. <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">The queen's</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragons</a> were fond of you, were they not?<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Ben_Plumm\" title=\"Ben Plumm\">Ben Plumm</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family\">Family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Viserys_Plumm&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Family\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div style=\"overflow:auto;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:separate;font-size:90%;line-height:100%;\">\n<tbody><tr align=\"center\"><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\"><a href=\"/index.php/Ossifer_Plumm\" title=\"Ossifer Plumm\">Ossifer</a></td><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:2em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\"